92using namespace Qt::StringLiterals;
93
94static qreal qt_getDevicePixelRatio(const QWidget *widget)
95{
96 return widget ? widget->devicePixelRatio() : qApp->devicePixelRatio();
97}
98
99/*!
100 \class QCommonStyle
101 \brief The QCommonStyle class encapsulates the common Look and Feel of a GUI.
102
103 \ingroup appearance
104 \inmodule QtWidgets
105
106 This abstract class implements some of the widget's look and feel
107 that is common to all GUI styles provided and shipped as part of
108 Qt.
109
110 Since QCommonStyle inherits QStyle, all of its functions are fully documented
111 in the QStyle documentation.
112 \omit
113 , although the
114 extra functions that QCommonStyle provides, e.g.
115 drawComplexControl(), drawControl(), drawPrimitive(),
116 hitTestComplexControl(), subControlRect(), sizeFromContents(), and
117 subElementRect() are documented here.
118 \endomit
119
120 \sa QStyle, QProxyStyle
121*/
122
123/*!
124 Constructs a QCommonStyle.
125*/
126QCommonStyle::QCommonStyle()
127 : QStyle(*new QCommonStylePrivate)
128{ }
129
130/*! \internal
131*/
132QCommonStyle::QCommonStyle(QCommonStylePrivate &dd)
133 : QStyle(dd)
134{ }
135
136/*!
137 Destroys the style.
138*/
139QCommonStyle::~QCommonStyle()
140{ }
141
142
143/*!
144 \reimp
145*/
146void QCommonStyle::drawPrimitive(PrimitiveElement pe, const QStyleOption *opt, QPainter *p,
147 const QWidget *widget) const
148{
149 Q_D(const QCommonStyle);
150 switch (pe) {
151 case PE_FrameButtonBevel:
152 case PE_FrameButtonTool:
153 qDrawShadeRect(p, r: opt->rect, pal: opt->palette,
154 sunken: opt->state & (State_Sunken | State_On), lineWidth: 1, midLineWidth: 0);
155 break;
156 case PE_PanelButtonCommand:
157 case PE_PanelButtonBevel:
158 case PE_PanelButtonTool:
159 case PE_IndicatorButtonDropDown:
160 qDrawShadePanel(p, r: opt->rect, pal: opt->palette,
161 sunken: opt->state & (State_Sunken | State_On), lineWidth: 1,
162 fill: &opt->palette.brush(cr: QPalette::Button));
163 break;
164 case PE_IndicatorItemViewItemCheck:
165 proxy()->drawPrimitive(pe: PE_IndicatorCheckBox, opt, p, w: widget);
166 break;
167 case PE_IndicatorCheckBox:
168 if (opt->state & State_NoChange) {
169 p->setPen(opt->palette.windowText().color());
170 p->fillRect(opt->rect, opt->palette.brush(cr: QPalette::Button));
171 p->drawRect(r: opt->rect);
172 p->drawLine(p1: opt->rect.topLeft(), p2: opt->rect.bottomRight());
173 } else {
174 qDrawShadePanel(p, x: opt->rect.x(), y: opt->rect.y(), w: opt->rect.width(), h: opt->rect.height(),
175 pal: opt->palette, sunken: opt->state & (State_Sunken | State_On), lineWidth: 1,
176 fill: &opt->palette.brush(cr: QPalette::Button));
177 }
178 break;
179 case PE_IndicatorRadioButton: {
180 QRect ir = opt->rect;
181 p->setPen(opt->palette.dark().color());
182 p->drawArc(r: opt->rect, a: 0, alen: 5760);
183 if (opt->state & (State_Sunken | State_On)) {
184 ir.adjust(dx1: 2, dy1: 2, dx2: -2, dy2: -2);
185 p->setBrush(opt->palette.windowText());
186 p->drawEllipse(r: ir);
187 }
188 break; }
189 case PE_FrameFocusRect:
190 if (const QStyleOptionFocusRect *fropt = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionFocusRect *>(opt)) {
191 QColor bg = fropt->backgroundColor;
192 QPen oldPen = p->pen();
193 if (bg.isValid()) {
194 int h, s, v;
195 bg.getHsv(h: &h, s: &s, v: &v);
196 if (v >= 128)
197 p->setPen(Qt::black);
198 else
199 p->setPen(Qt::white);
200 } else {
201 p->setPen(opt->palette.windowText().color());
202 }
203 QRect focusRect = opt->rect.adjusted(xp1: 1, yp1: 1, xp2: -1, yp2: -1);
204 p->drawRect(r: focusRect.adjusted(xp1: 0, yp1: 0, xp2: -1, yp2: -1)); //draw pen inclusive
205 p->setPen(oldPen);
206 }
207 break;
208 case PE_IndicatorMenuCheckMark: {
209 const int markW = opt->rect.width() > 7 ? 7 : opt->rect.width();
210 const int markH = markW;
211 int posX = opt->rect.x() + (opt->rect.width() - markW)/2 + 1;
212 int posY = opt->rect.y() + (opt->rect.height() - markH)/2;
213
214 QList<QLineF> a;
215 a.reserve(size: markH);
216
217 int i, xx, yy;
218 xx = posX;
219 yy = 3 + posY;
220 for (i = 0; i < markW/2; ++i) {
221 a << QLineF(xx, yy, xx, yy + 2);
222 ++xx;
223 ++yy;
224 }
225 yy -= 2;
226 for (; i < markH; ++i) {
227 a << QLineF(xx, yy, xx, yy + 2);
228 ++xx;
229 --yy;
230 }
231 if (!(opt->state & State_Enabled) && !(opt->state & State_On)) {
232 p->save();
233 p->translate(dx: 1, dy: 1);
234 p->setPen(opt->palette.light().color());
235 p->drawLines(lines: a);
236 p->restore();
237 }
238 p->setPen((opt->state & State_On) ? opt->palette.highlightedText().color() : opt->palette.text().color());
239 p->drawLines(lines: a);
240 break; }
241 case PE_Frame:
242 case PE_FrameMenu:
243 if (const QStyleOptionFrame *frame = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionFrame *>(opt)) {
244 if (pe == PE_FrameMenu || (frame->state & State_Sunken) || (frame->state & State_Raised)) {
245 qDrawShadePanel(p, r: frame->rect, pal: frame->palette, sunken: frame->state & State_Sunken,
246 lineWidth: frame->lineWidth);
247 } else {
248 qDrawPlainRect(p, r: frame->rect, frame->palette.windowText().color(), lineWidth: frame->lineWidth);
249 }
250 }
251 break;
252#if QT_CONFIG(toolbar)
253 case PE_PanelMenuBar:
254 if (widget && qobject_cast<QToolBar *>(object: widget->parentWidget()))
255 break;
256 if (const QStyleOptionFrame *frame = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionFrame *>(opt)){
257 qDrawShadePanel(p, r: frame->rect, pal: frame->palette, sunken: false, lineWidth: frame->lineWidth,
258 fill: &frame->palette.brush(cr: QPalette::Button));
259
260 }
261 else if (const QStyleOptionToolBar *frame = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionToolBar *>(opt)){
262 qDrawShadePanel(p, r: frame->rect, pal: frame->palette, sunken: false, lineWidth: frame->lineWidth,
263 fill: &frame->palette.brush(cr: QPalette::Button));
264 }
265
266 break;
267 case PE_PanelMenu:
268 break;
269 case PE_PanelToolBar:
270 break;
271#endif // QT_CONFIG(toolbar)
272#if QT_CONFIG(progressbar)
273 case PE_IndicatorProgressChunk:
274 {
275 bool vertical = false;
276 if (const QStyleOptionProgressBar *pb = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionProgressBar *>(opt))
277 vertical = !(pb->state & QStyle::State_Horizontal);
278 if (!vertical) {
279 p->fillRect(x: opt->rect.x(), y: opt->rect.y() + 3, w: opt->rect.width() -2, h: opt->rect.height() - 6,
280 b: opt->palette.brush(cr: QPalette::Highlight));
281 } else {
282 p->fillRect(x: opt->rect.x() + 2, y: opt->rect.y(), w: opt->rect.width() -6, h: opt->rect.height() - 2,
283 b: opt->palette.brush(cr: QPalette::Highlight));
284 }
285 }
286 break;
287#endif // QT_CONFIG(progressbar)
288 case PE_IndicatorBranch: {
289 static const int decoration_size = 9;
290 int mid_h = opt->rect.x() + opt->rect.width() / 2;
291 int mid_v = opt->rect.y() + opt->rect.height() / 2;
292 int bef_h = mid_h;
293 int bef_v = mid_v;
294 int aft_h = mid_h;
295 int aft_v = mid_v;
296 if (opt->state & State_Children) {
297 int delta = decoration_size / 2;
298 bef_h -= delta;
299 bef_v -= delta;
300 aft_h += delta;
301 aft_v += delta;
302 p->drawLine(x1: bef_h + 2, y1: bef_v + 4, x2: bef_h + 6, y2: bef_v + 4);
303 if (!(opt->state & State_Open))
304 p->drawLine(x1: bef_h + 4, y1: bef_v + 2, x2: bef_h + 4, y2: bef_v + 6);
305 QPen oldPen = p->pen();
306 p->setPen(opt->palette.dark().color());
307 p->drawRect(x: bef_h, y: bef_v, w: decoration_size - 1, h: decoration_size - 1);
308 p->setPen(oldPen);
309 }
310 QBrush brush(opt->palette.dark().color(), Qt::Dense4Pattern);
311 if (opt->state & State_Item) {
312 if (opt->direction == Qt::RightToLeft)
313 p->fillRect(x: opt->rect.left(), y: mid_v, w: bef_h - opt->rect.left(), h: 1, b: brush);
314 else
315 p->fillRect(x: aft_h, y: mid_v, w: opt->rect.right() - aft_h + 1, h: 1, b: brush);
316 }
317 if (opt->state & State_Sibling)
318 p->fillRect(x: mid_h, y: aft_v, w: 1, h: opt->rect.bottom() - aft_v + 1, b: brush);
319 if (opt->state & (State_Open | State_Children | State_Item | State_Sibling))
320 p->fillRect(x: mid_h, y: opt->rect.y(), w: 1, h: bef_v - opt->rect.y(), b: brush);
321 break; }
322 case PE_FrameStatusBarItem:
323 qDrawShadeRect(p, r: opt->rect, pal: opt->palette, sunken: true, lineWidth: 1, midLineWidth: 0, fill: nullptr);
324 break;
325 case PE_IndicatorHeaderArrow:
326 if (const QStyleOptionHeader *header = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionHeader *>(opt)) {
327 QPen oldPen = p->pen();
328 if (header->sortIndicator & QStyleOptionHeader::SortUp) {
329 p->setPen(QPen(opt->palette.light(), 0));
330 p->drawLine(x1: opt->rect.x() + opt->rect.width(), y1: opt->rect.y(),
331 x2: opt->rect.x() + opt->rect.width() / 2, y2: opt->rect.y() + opt->rect.height());
332 p->setPen(QPen(opt->palette.dark(), 0));
333 const QPoint points[] = {
334 QPoint(opt->rect.x() + opt->rect.width() / 2, opt->rect.y() + opt->rect.height()),
335 QPoint(opt->rect.x(), opt->rect.y()),
336 QPoint(opt->rect.x() + opt->rect.width(), opt->rect.y()),
337 };
338 p->drawPolyline(points, pointCount: sizeof points / sizeof *points);
339 } else if (header->sortIndicator & QStyleOptionHeader::SortDown) {
340 p->setPen(QPen(opt->palette.light(), 0));
341 const QPoint points[] = {
342 QPoint(opt->rect.x(), opt->rect.y() + opt->rect.height()),
343 QPoint(opt->rect.x() + opt->rect.width(), opt->rect.y() + opt->rect.height()),
344 QPoint(opt->rect.x() + opt->rect.width() / 2, opt->rect.y()),
345 };
346 p->drawPolyline(points, pointCount: sizeof points / sizeof *points);
347 p->setPen(QPen(opt->palette.dark(), 0));
348 p->drawLine(x1: opt->rect.x(), y1: opt->rect.y() + opt->rect.height(),
349 x2: opt->rect.x() + opt->rect.width() / 2, y2: opt->rect.y());
350 }
351 p->setPen(oldPen);
352 }
353 break;
354#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
355 case PE_FrameTabBarBase:
356 if (const QStyleOptionTabBarBase *tbb
357 = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionTabBarBase *>(opt)) {
358 p->save();
359 switch (tbb->shape) {
360 case QTabBar::RoundedNorth:
361 case QTabBar::TriangularNorth:
362 p->setPen(QPen(tbb->palette.light(), 0));
363 p->drawLine(p1: tbb->rect.topLeft(), p2: tbb->rect.topRight());
364 break;
365 case QTabBar::RoundedWest:
366 case QTabBar::TriangularWest:
367 p->setPen(QPen(tbb->palette.light(), 0));
368 p->drawLine(p1: tbb->rect.topLeft(), p2: tbb->rect.bottomLeft());
369 break;
370 case QTabBar::RoundedSouth:
371 case QTabBar::TriangularSouth:
372 p->setPen(QPen(tbb->palette.shadow(), 0));
373 p->drawLine(x1: tbb->rect.left(), y1: tbb->rect.bottom(),
374 x2: tbb->rect.right(), y2: tbb->rect.bottom());
375 p->setPen(QPen(tbb->palette.dark(), 0));
376 p->drawLine(x1: tbb->rect.left(), y1: tbb->rect.bottom() - 1,
377 x2: tbb->rect.right() - 1, y2: tbb->rect.bottom() - 1);
378 break;
379 case QTabBar::RoundedEast:
380 case QTabBar::TriangularEast:
381 p->setPen(QPen(tbb->palette.dark(), 0));
382 p->drawLine(p1: tbb->rect.topRight(), p2: tbb->rect.bottomRight());
383 break;
384 }
385 p->restore();
386 }
387 break;
388 case PE_IndicatorTabClose: {
389 if (d->tabBarcloseButtonIcon.isNull())
390 d->tabBarcloseButtonIcon = proxy()->standardIcon(standardIcon: QStyle::SP_TabCloseButton, option: opt, widget);
391
392 const int size = proxy()->pixelMetric(metric: QStyle::PM_SmallIconSize, option: opt);
393 QIcon::Mode mode = opt->state & State_Enabled ?
394 (opt->state & State_Raised ? QIcon::Active : QIcon::Normal)
395 : QIcon::Disabled;
396 if (!(opt->state & State_Raised)
397 && !(opt->state & State_Sunken)
398 && !(opt->state & QStyle::State_Selected))
399 mode = QIcon::Disabled;
400
401 QIcon::State state = opt->state & State_Sunken ? QIcon::On : QIcon::Off;
402 QPixmap pixmap = d->tabBarcloseButtonIcon.pixmap(size: QSize(size, size), devicePixelRatio: p->device()->devicePixelRatio(), mode, state);
403 proxy()->drawItemPixmap(painter: p, rect: opt->rect, alignment: Qt::AlignCenter, pixmap);
404 break;
405 }
406#else
407 Q_UNUSED(d);
408#endif // QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
409 case PE_FrameTabWidget:
410 case PE_FrameWindow:
411 qDrawWinPanel(p, r: opt->rect, pal: opt->palette, sunken: false, fill: nullptr);
412 break;
413 case PE_FrameLineEdit:
414 proxy()->drawPrimitive(pe: PE_Frame, opt, p, w: widget);
415 break;
416#if QT_CONFIG(groupbox)
417 case PE_FrameGroupBox:
418 if (const QStyleOptionFrame *frame = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionFrame *>(opt)) {
419 if (frame->features & QStyleOptionFrame::Flat) {
420 QRect fr = frame->rect;
421 QPoint p1(fr.x(), fr.y() + 1);
422 QPoint p2(fr.x() + fr.width(), p1.y());
423 qDrawShadeLine(p, p1, p2, pal: frame->palette, sunken: true,
424 lineWidth: frame->lineWidth, midLineWidth: frame->midLineWidth);
425 } else {
426 qDrawShadeRect(p, x: frame->rect.x(), y: frame->rect.y(), w: frame->rect.width(),
427 h: frame->rect.height(), pal: frame->palette, sunken: true,
428 lineWidth: frame->lineWidth, midLineWidth: frame->midLineWidth);
429 }
430 }
431 break;
432#endif // QT_CONFIG(groupbox)
433#if QT_CONFIG(dockwidget)
434 case PE_FrameDockWidget:
435 if (const QStyleOptionFrame *frame = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionFrame *>(opt)) {
436 int lw = frame->lineWidth;
437 if (lw <= 0)
438 lw = proxy()->pixelMetric(metric: PM_DockWidgetFrameWidth, option: opt);
439
440 qDrawShadePanel(p, r: frame->rect, pal: frame->palette, sunken: false, lineWidth: lw);
441 }
442 break;
443#endif // QT_CONFIG(dockwidget)
444#if QT_CONFIG(toolbar)
445 case PE_IndicatorToolBarHandle:
446 p->save();
447 p->translate(dx: opt->rect.x(), dy: opt->rect.y());
448 if (opt->state & State_Horizontal) {
449 int x = opt->rect.width() / 3;
450 if (opt->direction == Qt::RightToLeft)
451 x -= 2;
452 if (opt->rect.height() > 4) {
453 qDrawShadePanel(p, x, y: 2, w: 3, h: opt->rect.height() - 4,
454 pal: opt->palette, sunken: false, lineWidth: 1, fill: nullptr);
455 qDrawShadePanel(p, x: x+3, y: 2, w: 3, h: opt->rect.height() - 4,
456 pal: opt->palette, sunken: false, lineWidth: 1, fill: nullptr);
457 }
458 } else {
459 if (opt->rect.width() > 4) {
460 int y = opt->rect.height() / 3;
461 qDrawShadePanel(p, x: 2, y, w: opt->rect.width() - 4, h: 3,
462 pal: opt->palette, sunken: false, lineWidth: 1, fill: nullptr);
463 qDrawShadePanel(p, x: 2, y: y+3, w: opt->rect.width() - 4, h: 3,
464 pal: opt->palette, sunken: false, lineWidth: 1, fill: nullptr);
465 }
466 }
467 p->restore();
468 break;
469 case PE_IndicatorToolBarSeparator:
470 {
471 QPoint p1, p2;
472 if (opt->state & State_Horizontal) {
473 p1 = QPoint(opt->rect.width()/2, 0);
474 p2 = QPoint(p1.x(), opt->rect.height());
475 } else {
476 p1 = QPoint(0, opt->rect.height()/2);
477 p2 = QPoint(opt->rect.width(), p1.y());
478 }
479 qDrawShadeLine(p, p1, p2, pal: opt->palette, sunken: 1, lineWidth: 1, midLineWidth: 0);
480 break;
481 }
482#endif // QT_CONFIG(toolbar)
483#if QT_CONFIG(spinbox)
484 case PE_IndicatorSpinPlus:
485 case PE_IndicatorSpinMinus: {
486 QRect r = opt->rect;
487 int fw = proxy()->pixelMetric(metric: PM_DefaultFrameWidth, option: opt, widget);
488 QRect br = r.adjusted(xp1: fw, yp1: fw, xp2: -fw, yp2: -fw);
489
490 int offset = (opt->state & State_Sunken) ? 1 : 0;
491 int step = (br.width() + 4) / 5;
492 p->fillRect(x: br.x() + offset, y: br.y() + offset +br.height() / 2 - step / 2,
493 w: br.width(), h: step,
494 b: opt->palette.buttonText());
495 if (pe == PE_IndicatorSpinPlus)
496 p->fillRect(x: br.x() + br.width() / 2 - step / 2 + offset, y: br.y() + offset,
497 w: step, h: br.height(),
498 b: opt->palette.buttonText());
499
500 break; }
501 case PE_IndicatorSpinUp:
502 case PE_IndicatorSpinDown: {
503 QRect r = opt->rect;
504 int fw = proxy()->pixelMetric(metric: PM_DefaultFrameWidth, option: opt, widget);
505 // QRect br = r.adjusted(fw, fw, -fw, -fw);
506 int x = r.x(), y = r.y(), w = r.width(), h = r.height();
507 int sw = w-4;
508 if (sw < 3)
509 break;
510 else if (!(sw & 1))
511 sw--;
512 sw -= (sw / 7) * 2; // Empty border
513 int sh = sw/2 + 2; // Must have empty row at foot of arrow
514
515 int sx = x + w / 2 - sw / 2;
516 int sy = y + h / 2 - sh / 2;
517
518 if (pe == PE_IndicatorSpinUp && fw)
519 --sy;
520
521 int bsx = 0;
522 int bsy = 0;
523 if (opt->state & State_Sunken) {
524 bsx = proxy()->pixelMetric(metric: PM_ButtonShiftHorizontal, option: opt);
525 bsy = proxy()->pixelMetric(metric: PM_ButtonShiftVertical, option: opt);
526 }
527 p->save();
528 p->translate(dx: sx + bsx, dy: sy + bsy);
529 p->setPen(opt->palette.buttonText().color());
530 p->setBrush(opt->palette.buttonText());
531 if (pe == PE_IndicatorSpinDown) {
532 const QPoint points[] = { QPoint(0, 1), QPoint(sw-1, 1), QPoint(sh-2, sh-1) };
533 p->drawPolygon(points, pointCount: sizeof points / sizeof *points);
534 } else {
535 const QPoint points[] = { QPoint(0, sh-1), QPoint(sw-1, sh-1), QPoint(sh-2, 1) };
536 p->drawPolygon(points, pointCount: sizeof points / sizeof *points);
537 }
538 p->restore();
539 break; }
540#endif // QT_CONFIG(spinbox)
541 case PE_PanelTipLabel: {
542 const QBrush brush(opt->palette.toolTipBase());
543 qDrawPlainRect(p, r: opt->rect, opt->palette.toolTipText().color(), lineWidth: 1, fill: &brush);
544 break;
545 }
546#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
547 case PE_IndicatorTabTear:
548 if (const QStyleOptionTab *tab = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionTab *>(opt)) {
549 bool rtl = tab->direction == Qt::RightToLeft;
550 const bool horizontal = tab->rect.height() > tab->rect.width();
551 const int margin = 4;
552 QPainterPath path;
553
554 if (horizontal) {
555 QRect rect = tab->rect.adjusted(xp1: rtl ? margin : 0, yp1: 0, xp2: rtl ? 1 : -margin, yp2: 0);
556 rect.setTop(rect.top() + ((tab->state & State_Selected) ? 1 : 3));
557 rect.setBottom(rect.bottom() - ((tab->state & State_Selected) ? 0 : 2));
558
559 path.moveTo(p: QPoint(rtl ? rect.right() : rect.left(), rect.top()));
560 int count = 4;
561 for (int jags = 1; jags <= count; ++jags, rtl = !rtl)
562 path.lineTo(p: QPoint(rtl ? rect.left() : rect.right(), rect.top() + jags * rect.height()/count));
563 } else {
564 QRect rect = tab->rect.adjusted(xp1: 0, yp1: 0, xp2: 0, yp2: -margin);
565 rect.setLeft(rect.left() + ((tab->state & State_Selected) ? 1 : 3));
566 rect.setRight(rect.right() - ((tab->state & State_Selected) ? 0 : 2));
567
568 path.moveTo(p: QPoint(rect.left(), rect.top()));
569 int count = 4;
570 for (int jags = 1; jags <= count; ++jags, rtl = !rtl)
571 path.lineTo(p: QPoint(rect.left() + jags * rect.width()/count, rtl ? rect.top() : rect.bottom()));
572 }
573
574 p->setPen(QPen(tab->palette.dark(), qreal(.8)));
575 p->setBrush(tab->palette.window());
576 p->setRenderHint(hint: QPainter::Antialiasing);
577 p->drawPath(path);
578 }
579 break;
580#endif // QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
581#if QT_CONFIG(lineedit)
582 case PE_PanelLineEdit:
583 if (const QStyleOptionFrame *panel = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionFrame *>(opt)) {
584 p->fillRect(panel->rect.adjusted(xp1: panel->lineWidth, yp1: panel->lineWidth, xp2: -panel->lineWidth, yp2: -panel->lineWidth),
585 panel->palette.brush(cr: QPalette::Base));
586
587 if (panel->lineWidth > 0)
588 proxy()->drawPrimitive(pe: PE_FrameLineEdit, opt: panel, p, w: widget);
589 }
590 break;
591#endif // QT_CONFIG(lineedit)
592#if QT_CONFIG(columnview)
593 case PE_IndicatorColumnViewArrow: {
594 if (const QStyleOptionViewItem *viewOpt = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionViewItem *>(opt)) {
595 bool reverse = (viewOpt->direction == Qt::RightToLeft);
596 p->save();
597 QPainterPath path;
598 int x = viewOpt->rect.x() + 1;
599 int offset = (viewOpt->rect.height() / 3);
600 int height = (viewOpt->rect.height()) - offset * 2;
601 if (height % 2 == 1)
602 --height;
603 int x2 = x + height - 1;
604 if (reverse) {
605 x = viewOpt->rect.x() + viewOpt->rect.width() - 1;
606 x2 = x - height + 1;
607 }
608 path.moveTo(x, y: viewOpt->rect.y() + offset);
609 path.lineTo(x, y: viewOpt->rect.y() + offset + height);
610 path.lineTo(x: x2, y: viewOpt->rect.y() + offset+height/2);
611 path.closeSubpath();
612 if (viewOpt->state & QStyle::State_Selected ) {
613 if (viewOpt->showDecorationSelected) {
614 QColor color = viewOpt->palette.color(cg: QPalette::Active, cr: QPalette::HighlightedText);
615 p->setPen(color);
616 p->setBrush(color);
617 } else {
618 QColor color = viewOpt->palette.color(cg: QPalette::Active, cr: QPalette::WindowText);
619 p->setPen(color);
620 p->setBrush(color);
621 }
622
623 } else {
624 QColor color = viewOpt->palette.color(cg: QPalette::Active, cr: QPalette::Mid);
625 p->setPen(color);
626 p->setBrush(color);
627 }
628 p->drawPath(path);
629
630 // draw the vertical and top triangle line
631 if (!(viewOpt->state & QStyle::State_Selected)) {
632 QPainterPath lines;
633 lines.moveTo(x, y: viewOpt->rect.y() + offset);
634 lines.lineTo(x, y: viewOpt->rect.y() + offset + height);
635 lines.moveTo(x, y: viewOpt->rect.y() + offset);
636 lines.lineTo(x: x2, y: viewOpt->rect.y() + offset+height/2);
637 QColor color = viewOpt->palette.color(cg: QPalette::Active, cr: QPalette::Dark);
638 p->setPen(color);
639 p->drawPath(path: lines);
640 }
641 p->restore();
642 }
643 break; }
644#endif //QT_CONFIG(columnview)
645 case PE_IndicatorItemViewItemDrop: {
646 QRect rect = opt->rect;
647 if (opt->rect.height() == 0)
648 p->drawLine(p1: rect.topLeft(), p2: rect.topRight());
649 else
650 p->drawRect(r: rect);
651 break; }
652#if QT_CONFIG(itemviews)
653 case PE_PanelItemViewRow:
654 if (const QStyleOptionViewItem *vopt = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionViewItem *>(opt)) {
655 QPalette::ColorGroup cg = (widget ? widget->isEnabled() : (vopt->state & QStyle::State_Enabled))
656 ? QPalette::Normal : QPalette::Disabled;
657 if (cg == QPalette::Normal && !(vopt->state & QStyle::State_Active))
658 cg = QPalette::Inactive;
659
660 if ((vopt->state & QStyle::State_Selected) && vopt->showDecorationSelected)
661 p->fillRect(vopt->rect, vopt->palette.brush(cg, cr: QPalette::Highlight));
662 else if (vopt->features & QStyleOptionViewItem::Alternate)
663 p->fillRect(vopt->rect, vopt->palette.brush(cg, cr: QPalette::AlternateBase));
664 }
665 break;
666 case PE_PanelItemViewItem:
667 if (const QStyleOptionViewItem *vopt = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionViewItem *>(opt)) {
668 QPalette::ColorGroup cg = (widget ? widget->isEnabled() : (vopt->state & QStyle::State_Enabled))
669 ? QPalette::Normal : QPalette::Disabled;
670 if (cg == QPalette::Normal && !(vopt->state & QStyle::State_Active))
671 cg = QPalette::Inactive;
672
673 if (vopt->showDecorationSelected && (vopt->state & QStyle::State_Selected)) {
674 p->fillRect(vopt->rect, vopt->palette.brush(cg, cr: QPalette::Highlight));
675 } else {
676 if (vopt->backgroundBrush.style() != Qt::NoBrush) {
677 QPointF oldBO = p->brushOrigin();
678 p->setBrushOrigin(vopt->rect.topLeft());
679 p->fillRect(vopt->rect, vopt->backgroundBrush);
680 p->setBrushOrigin(oldBO);
681 }
682
683 if (vopt->state & QStyle::State_Selected) {
684 QRect textRect = subElementRect(r: QStyle::SE_ItemViewItemText, opt, widget);
685 p->fillRect(textRect, vopt->palette.brush(cg, cr: QPalette::Highlight));
686 }
687 }
688 }
689 break;
690#endif // QT_CONFIG(itemviews)
691 case PE_PanelScrollAreaCorner: {
692 const QBrush brush(opt->palette.brush(cr: QPalette::Window));
693 p->fillRect(opt->rect, brush);
694 } break;
695 case PE_IndicatorArrowUp:
696 case PE_IndicatorArrowDown:
697 case PE_IndicatorArrowRight:
698 case PE_IndicatorArrowLeft:
699 {
700 if (opt->rect.width() <= 1 || opt->rect.height() <= 1)
701 break;
702 QRect r = opt->rect;
703 int size = qMin(a: r.height(), b: r.width());
704 QPixmap pixmap;
705 QString pixmapName =
706 QStyleHelper::uniqueName(key: "$qt_ia-"_L1
707 % QLatin1StringView(metaObject()->className()),
708 option: opt, size: QSize(size, size))
709 % HexString<uint>(pe);
710 if (!QPixmapCache::find(key: pixmapName, pixmap: &pixmap)) {
711 qreal pixelRatio = p->device()->devicePixelRatio();
712 int border = qRound(d: pixelRatio*(size/5));
713 int sqsize = qRound(d: pixelRatio*(2*(size/2)));
714 QImage image(sqsize, sqsize, QImage::Format_ARGB32_Premultiplied);
715 image.fill(pixel: 0);
716 QPainter imagePainter(&image);
717
718 QPolygon a;
719 switch (pe) {
720 case PE_IndicatorArrowUp:
721 a.setPoints(nPoints: 3, firstx: border, firsty: sqsize/2, sqsize/2, border, sqsize - border, sqsize/2);
722 break;
723 case PE_IndicatorArrowDown:
724 a.setPoints(nPoints: 3, firstx: border, firsty: sqsize/2, sqsize/2, sqsize - border, sqsize - border, sqsize/2);
725 break;
726 case PE_IndicatorArrowRight:
727 a.setPoints(nPoints: 3, firstx: sqsize - border, firsty: sqsize/2, sqsize/2, border, sqsize/2, sqsize - border);
728 break;
729 case PE_IndicatorArrowLeft:
730 a.setPoints(nPoints: 3, firstx: border, firsty: sqsize/2, sqsize/2, border, sqsize/2, sqsize - border);
731 break;
732 default:
733 break;
734 }
735
736 int bsx = 0;
737 int bsy = 0;
738
739 if (opt->state & State_Sunken) {
740 bsx = proxy()->pixelMetric(metric: PM_ButtonShiftHorizontal, option: opt, widget);
741 bsy = proxy()->pixelMetric(metric: PM_ButtonShiftVertical, option: opt, widget);
742 }
743
744 QRect bounds = a.boundingRect();
745 int sx = sqsize / 2 - bounds.center().x() - 1;
746 int sy = sqsize / 2 - bounds.center().y() - 1;
747 imagePainter.translate(dx: sx + bsx, dy: sy + bsy);
748 imagePainter.setPen(opt->palette.buttonText().color());
749 imagePainter.setBrush(opt->palette.buttonText());
750
751 if (!(opt->state & State_Enabled)) {
752 imagePainter.translate(dx: 1, dy: 1);
753 imagePainter.setBrush(opt->palette.light().color());
754 imagePainter.setPen(opt->palette.light().color());
755 imagePainter.drawPolygon(polygon: a);
756 imagePainter.translate(dx: -1, dy: -1);
757 imagePainter.setBrush(opt->palette.mid().color());
758 imagePainter.setPen(opt->palette.mid().color());
759 }
760
761 imagePainter.drawPolygon(polygon: a);
762 imagePainter.end();
763 pixmap = QPixmap::fromImage(image);
764 pixmap.setDevicePixelRatio(pixelRatio);
765 QPixmapCache::insert(key: pixmapName, pixmap);
766 }
767 int xOffset = r.x() + (r.width() - size)/2;
768 int yOffset = r.y() + (r.height() - size)/2;
769 p->drawPixmap(x: xOffset, y: yOffset, pm: pixmap);
770 }
771 break;
772 default:
773 break;
774 }
775}

777#if QT_CONFIG(toolbutton)
778static void drawArrow(const QStyle *style, const QStyleOptionToolButton *toolbutton,
779 const QRect &rect, QPainter *painter, const QWidget *widget = nullptr)
780{
781 QStyle::PrimitiveElement pe;
782 switch (toolbutton->arrowType) {
783 case Qt::LeftArrow:
784 pe = QStyle::PE_IndicatorArrowLeft;
785 break;
786 case Qt::RightArrow:
787 pe = QStyle::PE_IndicatorArrowRight;
788 break;
789 case Qt::UpArrow:
790 pe = QStyle::PE_IndicatorArrowUp;
791 break;
792 case Qt::DownArrow:
793 pe = QStyle::PE_IndicatorArrowDown;
794 break;
795 default:
796 return;
797 }
798 QStyleOption arrowOpt = *toolbutton;
799 arrowOpt.rect = rect;
800 style->drawPrimitive(pe, opt: &arrowOpt, p: painter, w: widget);
801}
802#endif // QT_CONFIG(toolbutton)
803
804static QSizeF viewItemTextLayout(QTextLayout &textLayout, int lineWidth, int maxHeight = -1, int *lastVisibleLine = nullptr)
805{
806 if (lastVisibleLine)
807 *lastVisibleLine = -1;
808 qreal height = 0;
809 qreal widthUsed = 0;
810 textLayout.beginLayout();
811 int i = 0;
812 while (true) {
813 QTextLine line = textLayout.createLine();
814 if (!line.isValid())
815 break;
816 line.setLineWidth(lineWidth);
817 line.setPosition(QPointF(0, height));
818 height += line.height();
819 widthUsed = qMax(a: widthUsed, b: line.naturalTextWidth());
820 // we assume that the height of the next line is the same as the current one
821 if (maxHeight > 0 && lastVisibleLine && height + line.height() > maxHeight) {
822 const QTextLine nextLine = textLayout.createLine();
823 *lastVisibleLine = nextLine.isValid() ? i : -1;
824 break;
825 }
826 ++i;
827 }
828 textLayout.endLayout();
829 return QSizeF(widthUsed, height);
830}
831
832QString QCommonStylePrivate::calculateElidedText(const QString &text, const QTextOption &textOption,
833 const QFont &font, const QRect &textRect, const Qt::Alignment valign,
834 Qt::TextElideMode textElideMode, int flags,
835 bool lastVisibleLineShouldBeElided, QPointF *paintStartPosition) const
836{
837 QTextLayout textLayout(text, font);
838 textLayout.setTextOption(textOption);
839
840 // In AlignVCenter mode when more than one line is displayed and the height only allows
841 // some of the lines it makes no sense to display those. From a users perspective it makes
842 // more sense to see the start of the text instead something inbetween.
843 const bool vAlignmentOptimization = paintStartPosition && valign.testFlag(flag: Qt::AlignVCenter);
844
845 int lastVisibleLine = -1;
846 viewItemTextLayout(textLayout, lineWidth: textRect.width(), maxHeight: vAlignmentOptimization ? textRect.height() : -1, lastVisibleLine: &lastVisibleLine);
847
848 const QRectF boundingRect = textLayout.boundingRect();
849 // don't care about LTR/RTL here, only need the height
850 const QRect layoutRect = QStyle::alignedRect(direction: Qt::LayoutDirectionAuto, alignment: valign,
851 size: boundingRect.size().toSize(), rectangle: textRect);
852
853 if (paintStartPosition)
854 *paintStartPosition = QPointF(textRect.x(), layoutRect.top());
855
856 QString ret;
857 qreal height = 0;
858 const int lineCount = textLayout.lineCount();
859 for (int i = 0; i < lineCount; ++i) {
860 const QTextLine line = textLayout.lineAt(i);
861 height += line.height();
862
863 // above visible rect
864 if (height + layoutRect.top() <= textRect.top()) {
865 if (paintStartPosition)
866 paintStartPosition->ry() += line.height();
867 continue;
868 }
869
870 const int start = line.textStart();
871 const int length = line.textLength();
872 const bool drawElided = line.naturalTextWidth() > textRect.width();
873 bool elideLastVisibleLine = lastVisibleLine == i;
874 if (!drawElided && i + 1 < lineCount && lastVisibleLineShouldBeElided) {
875 const QTextLine nextLine = textLayout.lineAt(i: i + 1);
876 const int nextHeight = height + nextLine.height() / 2;
877 // elide when less than the next half line is visible
878 if (nextHeight + layoutRect.top() > textRect.height() + textRect.top())
879 elideLastVisibleLine = true;
880 }
881
882 QString text = textLayout.text().mid(position: start, n: length);
883 if (drawElided || elideLastVisibleLine) {
884 if (elideLastVisibleLine) {
885 if (text.endsWith(c: QChar::LineSeparator))
886 text.chop(n: 1);
887 text += QChar(0x2026);
888 }
889 const QStackTextEngine engine(text, font);
890 ret += engine.elidedText(mode: textElideMode, width: textRect.width(), flags);
891
892 // no newline for the last line (last visible or real)
893 // sometimes drawElided is true but no eliding is done so the text ends
894 // with QChar::LineSeparator - don't add another one. This happened with
895 // arabic text in the testcase for QTBUG-72805
896 if (i < lineCount - 1 &&
897 !ret.endsWith(c: QChar::LineSeparator))
898 ret += QChar::LineSeparator;
899 } else {
900 ret += text;
901 }
902
903 // below visible text, can stop
904 if ((height + layoutRect.top() >= textRect.bottom()) ||
905 (lastVisibleLine >= 0 && lastVisibleLine == i))
906 break;
907 }
908 return ret;
909}
910
911#if QT_CONFIG(itemviews)
912
913QSize QCommonStylePrivate::viewItemSize(const QStyleOptionViewItem *option, int role) const
914{
915 const QWidget *widget = option->widget;
916 switch (role) {
917 case Qt::CheckStateRole:
918 if (option->features & QStyleOptionViewItem::HasCheckIndicator)
919 return QSize(proxyStyle->pixelMetric(metric: QStyle::PM_IndicatorWidth, option, widget),
920 proxyStyle->pixelMetric(metric: QStyle::PM_IndicatorHeight, option, widget));
921 break;
922 case Qt::DisplayRole:
923 if (option->features & QStyleOptionViewItem::HasDisplay) {
924 QTextOption textOption;
925 textOption.setWrapMode(QTextOption::WordWrap);
926 QTextLayout textLayout(option->text, option->font);
927 textLayout.setTextOption(textOption);
928 const bool wrapText = option->features & QStyleOptionViewItem::WrapText;
929 const int textMargin = proxyStyle->pixelMetric(metric: QStyle::PM_FocusFrameHMargin, option, widget) + 1;
930 QRect bounds = option->rect;
931 switch (option->decorationPosition) {
932 case QStyleOptionViewItem::Left:
933 case QStyleOptionViewItem::Right: {
934 if (wrapText && bounds.isValid()) {
935 int width = bounds.width() - 2 * textMargin;
936 if (option->features & QStyleOptionViewItem::HasDecoration)
937 width -= option->decorationSize.width() + 2 * textMargin;
938 bounds.setWidth(width);
939 } else
940 bounds.setWidth(QFIXED_MAX);
941 break;
942 }
943 case QStyleOptionViewItem::Top:
944 case QStyleOptionViewItem::Bottom: {
945 int width;
946 if (wrapText) {
947 if (bounds.isValid())
948 width = bounds.width() - 2 * textMargin;
949 else if (option->features & QStyleOptionViewItem::HasDecoration)
950 width = option->decorationSize.width();
951 else
952 width = 0;
953 } else {
954 width = QFIXED_MAX;
955 }
956 bounds.setWidth(width);
957 break;
958 }
959 default:
960 break;
961 }
962
963 if (wrapText && option->features & QStyleOptionViewItem::HasCheckIndicator)
964 bounds.setWidth(bounds.width() - proxyStyle->pixelMetric(metric: QStyle::PM_IndicatorWidth, option) - 2 * textMargin);
965
966 const int lineWidth = bounds.width();
967 const QSizeF size = viewItemTextLayout(textLayout, lineWidth);
968 return QSize(qCeil(v: size.width()) + 2 * textMargin, qCeil(v: size.height()));
969 }
970 break;
971 case Qt::DecorationRole:
972 if (option->features & QStyleOptionViewItem::HasDecoration) {
973 return option->decorationSize;
974 }
975 break;
976 default:
977 break;
978 }
979
980 return QSize(0, 0);
981}
982
983void QCommonStylePrivate::viewItemDrawText(QPainter *p, const QStyleOptionViewItem *option, const QRect &rect) const
984{
985 const QWidget *widget = option->widget;
986 const int textMargin = proxyStyle->pixelMetric(metric: QStyle::PM_FocusFrameHMargin, option: nullptr, widget) + 1;
987
988 QRect textRect = rect.adjusted(xp1: textMargin, yp1: 0, xp2: -textMargin, yp2: 0); // remove width padding
989 const bool wrapText = option->features & QStyleOptionViewItem::WrapText;
990 QTextOption textOption;
991 textOption.setWrapMode(wrapText ? QTextOption::WordWrap : QTextOption::ManualWrap);
992 textOption.setTextDirection(option->direction);
993 textOption.setAlignment(QStyle::visualAlignment(direction: option->direction, alignment: option->displayAlignment));
994
995 QPointF paintPosition;
996 const QString newText = calculateElidedText(text: option->text, textOption,
997 font: option->font, textRect, valign: option->displayAlignment,
998 textElideMode: option->textElideMode, flags: 0,
999 lastVisibleLineShouldBeElided: true, paintStartPosition: &paintPosition);
1000
1001 QTextLayout textLayout(newText, option->font);
1002 textLayout.setTextOption(textOption);
1003 viewItemTextLayout(textLayout, lineWidth: textRect.width());
1004 textLayout.draw(p, pos: paintPosition);
1005}
1006
1007/*! \internal
1008 compute the position for the different component of an item (pixmap, text, checkbox)
1009
1010 Set sizehint to false to layout the elements inside opt->rect. Set sizehint to true to ignore
1011 opt->rect and return rectangles in infinite space
1012
1013 Code duplicated in QItemDelegate::doLayout
1014*/
1015void QCommonStylePrivate::viewItemLayout(const QStyleOptionViewItem *opt, QRect *checkRect,
1016 QRect *pixmapRect, QRect *textRect, bool sizehint) const
1017{
1018 Q_ASSERT(checkRect && pixmapRect && textRect);
1019 *pixmapRect = QRect(QPoint(0, 0), viewItemSize(option: opt, role: Qt::DecorationRole));
1020 *textRect = QRect(QPoint(0, 0), viewItemSize(option: opt, role: Qt::DisplayRole));
1021 *checkRect = QRect(QPoint(0, 0), viewItemSize(option: opt, role: Qt::CheckStateRole));
1022
1023 const QWidget *widget = opt->widget;
1024 const bool hasCheck = checkRect->isValid();
1025 const bool hasPixmap = pixmapRect->isValid();
1026 const bool hasText = textRect->isValid();
1027 const bool hasMargin = (hasText | hasPixmap | hasCheck);
1028 const int frameHMargin = hasMargin ?
1029 proxyStyle->pixelMetric(metric: QStyle::PM_FocusFrameHMargin, option: opt, widget) + 1 : 0;
1030 const int textMargin = hasText ? frameHMargin : 0;
1031 const int pixmapMargin = hasPixmap ? frameHMargin : 0;
1032 const int checkMargin = hasCheck ? frameHMargin : 0;
1033 const int x = opt->rect.left();
1034 const int y = opt->rect.top();
1035 int w, h;
1036
1037 if (textRect->height() == 0 && (!hasPixmap || !sizehint)) {
1038 //if there is no text, we still want to have a decent height for the item sizeHint and the editor size
1039 textRect->setHeight(opt->fontMetrics.height());
1040 }
1041
1042 QSize pm(0, 0);
1043 if (hasPixmap) {
1044 pm = pixmapRect->size();
1045 pm.rwidth() += 2 * pixmapMargin;
1046 }
1047 if (sizehint) {
1048 h = qMax(a: checkRect->height(), b: qMax(a: textRect->height(), b: pm.height()));
1049 if (opt->decorationPosition == QStyleOptionViewItem::Left
1050 || opt->decorationPosition == QStyleOptionViewItem::Right) {
1051 w = textRect->width() + pm.width();
1052 } else {
1053 w = qMax(a: textRect->width(), b: pm.width());
1054 }
1055 } else {
1056 w = opt->rect.width();
1057 h = opt->rect.height();
1058 }
1059
1060 int cw = 0;
1061 QRect check;
1062 if (hasCheck) {
1063 cw = checkRect->width() + 2 * checkMargin;
1064 if (sizehint) w += cw;
1065 if (opt->direction == Qt::RightToLeft) {
1066 check.setRect(ax: x + w - cw, ay: y, aw: cw, ah: h);
1067 } else {
1068 check.setRect(ax: x, ay: y, aw: cw, ah: h);
1069 }
1070 }
1071
1072 QRect display;
1073 QRect decoration;
1074 switch (opt->decorationPosition) {
1075 case QStyleOptionViewItem::Top: {
1076 if (hasPixmap)
1077 pm.setHeight(pm.height() + pixmapMargin); // add space
1078 h = sizehint ? textRect->height() : h - pm.height();
1079
1080 if (opt->direction == Qt::RightToLeft) {
1081 decoration.setRect(ax: x, ay: y, aw: w - cw, ah: pm.height());
1082 display.setRect(ax: x, ay: y + pm.height(), aw: w - cw, ah: h);
1083 } else {
1084 decoration.setRect(ax: x + cw, ay: y, aw: w - cw, ah: pm.height());
1085 display.setRect(ax: x + cw, ay: y + pm.height(), aw: w - cw, ah: h);
1086 }
1087 break; }
1088 case QStyleOptionViewItem::Bottom: {
1089 if (hasText)
1090 textRect->setHeight(textRect->height() + textMargin); // add space
1091 h = sizehint ? textRect->height() + pm.height() : h;
1092
1093 if (opt->direction == Qt::RightToLeft) {
1094 display.setRect(ax: x, ay: y, aw: w - cw, ah: textRect->height());
1095 decoration.setRect(ax: x, ay: y + textRect->height(), aw: w - cw, ah: h - textRect->height());
1096 } else {
1097 display.setRect(ax: x + cw, ay: y, aw: w - cw, ah: textRect->height());
1098 decoration.setRect(ax: x + cw, ay: y + textRect->height(), aw: w - cw, ah: h - textRect->height());
1099 }
1100 break; }
1101 case QStyleOptionViewItem::Left: {
1102 if (opt->direction == Qt::LeftToRight) {
1103 decoration.setRect(ax: x + cw, ay: y, aw: pm.width(), ah: h);
1104 display.setRect(ax: decoration.right() + 1, ay: y, aw: w - pm.width() - cw, ah: h);
1105 } else {
1106 display.setRect(ax: x, ay: y, aw: w - pm.width() - cw, ah: h);
1107 decoration.setRect(ax: display.right() + 1, ay: y, aw: pm.width(), ah: h);
1108 }
1109 break; }
1110 case QStyleOptionViewItem::Right: {
1111 if (opt->direction == Qt::LeftToRight) {
1112 display.setRect(ax: x + cw, ay: y, aw: w - pm.width() - cw, ah: h);
1113 decoration.setRect(ax: display.right() + 1, ay: y, aw: pm.width(), ah: h);
1114 } else {
1115 decoration.setRect(ax: x, ay: y, aw: pm.width(), ah: h);
1116 display.setRect(ax: decoration.right() + 1, ay: y, aw: w - pm.width() - cw, ah: h);
1117 }
1118 break; }
1119 default:
1120 qCWarning(lcCommonStyle, "doLayout: decoration position is invalid");
1121 decoration = *pixmapRect;
1122 break;
1123 }
1124
1125 if (!sizehint) { // we only need to do the internal layout if we are going to paint
1126 *checkRect = QStyle::alignedRect(direction: opt->direction, alignment: Qt::AlignCenter,
1127 size: checkRect->size(), rectangle: check);
1128 *pixmapRect = QStyle::alignedRect(direction: opt->direction, alignment: opt->decorationAlignment,
1129 size: pixmapRect->size(), rectangle: decoration);
1130 // the text takes up all available space, unless the decoration is not shown as selected
1131 if (opt->showDecorationSelected)
1132 *textRect = display;
1133 else
1134 *textRect = QStyle::alignedRect(direction: opt->direction, alignment: opt->displayAlignment,
1135 size: textRect->size().boundedTo(otherSize: display.size()), rectangle: display);
1136 } else {
1137 *checkRect = check;
1138 *pixmapRect = decoration;
1139 *textRect = display;
1140 }
1141}
1142#endif // QT_CONFIG(itemviews)
1143
1144#if QT_CONFIG(toolbutton)
1145QString QCommonStylePrivate::toolButtonElideText(const QStyleOptionToolButton *option,
1146 const QRect &textRect, int flags) const
1147{
1148 if (option->fontMetrics.horizontalAdvance(option->text) <= textRect.width())
1149 return option->text;
1150
1151 QString text = option->text;
1152 text.replace(before: u'\n', after: QChar::LineSeparator);
1153 QTextOption textOption;
1154 textOption.setWrapMode(QTextOption::ManualWrap);
1155 textOption.setTextDirection(option->direction);
1156
1157 return calculateElidedText(text, textOption,
1158 font: option->font, textRect, valign: Qt::AlignTop,
1159 textElideMode: Qt::ElideMiddle, flags,
1160 lastVisibleLineShouldBeElided: false, paintStartPosition: nullptr);
1161}
1162#endif // QT_CONFIG(toolbutton)
1163
1164#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1165/*! \internal
1166 Compute the textRect and the pixmapRect from the opt rect
1167
1168 Uses the same computation than in QTabBar::tabSizeHint
1169 */
1170void QCommonStylePrivate::tabLayout(const QStyleOptionTab *opt, const QWidget *widget, QRect *textRect, QRect *iconRect) const
1171{
1172 Q_ASSERT(textRect);
1173 Q_ASSERT(iconRect);
1174 QRect tr = opt->rect;
1175 bool verticalTabs = opt->shape == QTabBar::RoundedEast
1176 || opt->shape == QTabBar::RoundedWest
1177 || opt->shape == QTabBar::TriangularEast
1178 || opt->shape == QTabBar::TriangularWest;
1179 if (verticalTabs)
1180 tr.setRect(ax: 0, ay: 0, aw: tr.height(), ah: tr.width()); // 0, 0 as we will have a translate transform
1181
1182 int verticalShift = proxyStyle->pixelMetric(metric: QStyle::PM_TabBarTabShiftVertical, option: opt, widget);
1183 int horizontalShift = proxyStyle->pixelMetric(metric: QStyle::PM_TabBarTabShiftHorizontal, option: opt, widget);
1184 int hpadding = proxyStyle->pixelMetric(metric: QStyle::PM_TabBarTabHSpace, option: opt, widget) / 2;
1185 int vpadding = proxyStyle->pixelMetric(metric: QStyle::PM_TabBarTabVSpace, option: opt, widget) / 2;
1186 if (opt->shape == QTabBar::RoundedSouth || opt->shape == QTabBar::TriangularSouth)
1187 verticalShift = -verticalShift;
1188 tr.adjust(dx1: hpadding, dy1: verticalShift - vpadding, dx2: horizontalShift - hpadding, dy2: vpadding);
1189 bool selected = opt->state & QStyle::State_Selected;
1190 if (selected) {
1191 tr.setTop(tr.top() - verticalShift);
1192 tr.setRight(tr.right() - horizontalShift);
1193 }
1194
1195 // left widget
1196 if (!opt->leftButtonSize.isEmpty()) {
1197 tr.setLeft(tr.left() + 4 +
1198 (verticalTabs ? opt->leftButtonSize.height() : opt->leftButtonSize.width()));
1199 }
1200 // right widget
1201 if (!opt->rightButtonSize.isEmpty()) {
1202 tr.setRight(tr.right() - 4 -
1203 (verticalTabs ? opt->rightButtonSize.height() : opt->rightButtonSize.width()));
1204 }
1205
1206 // icon
1207 if (!opt->icon.isNull()) {
1208 QSize iconSize = opt->iconSize;
1209 if (!iconSize.isValid()) {
1210 int iconExtent = proxyStyle->pixelMetric(metric: QStyle::PM_SmallIconSize, option: opt);
1211 iconSize = QSize(iconExtent, iconExtent);
1212 }
1213 QSize tabIconSize = opt->icon.actualSize(size: iconSize,
1214 mode: (opt->state & QStyle::State_Enabled) ? QIcon::Normal : QIcon::Disabled,
1215 state: (opt->state & QStyle::State_Selected) ? QIcon::On : QIcon::Off);
1216 // High-dpi icons do not need adjustment; make sure tabIconSize is not larger than iconSize
1217 tabIconSize = QSize(qMin(a: tabIconSize.width(), b: iconSize.width()), qMin(a: tabIconSize.height(), b: iconSize.height()));
1218
1219 const int offsetX = (iconSize.width() - tabIconSize.width()) / 2;
1220 *iconRect = QRect(tr.left() + offsetX, tr.center().y() - tabIconSize.height() / 2,
1221 tabIconSize.width(), tabIconSize.height());
1222 if (!verticalTabs)
1223 *iconRect = QStyle::visualRect(direction: opt->direction, boundingRect: opt->rect, logicalRect: *iconRect);
1224 tr.setLeft(tr.left() + tabIconSize.width() + 4);
1225 }
1226
1227 if (!verticalTabs)
1228 tr = QStyle::visualRect(direction: opt->direction, boundingRect: opt->rect, logicalRect: tr);
1229
1230 *textRect = tr;
1231}
1232#endif // QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
